            "style": "",
            "text": ": In order to stop the climate crisis, Kate Aronoff writes we need to give up on the political and economic principle that the economy will continue to grow. Giving up on that idea — or pursuing “degrowth” — isn’t just necessary to save the climate, notes Aronoff, but also means that we will be able to work less and have more time for leisure.",
